  <prompt>
    Close ledger entry RB-T070-02 by adding `[JsonIgnore(Condition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull)]` to
    `CapabilityChangePayload.RetryAfterSeconds` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/R2SseEventEmitter.cs`.
    The property currently emits `"retryAfterSeconds": null` in the wire format when null; the documented contract requires the field to be omitted.

    Same family as RB-T050-01 (task 034). Same fix pattern.

    Production fix per ledger Recommended Fix section: add the property-level attribute to the record's `RetryAfterSeconds` parameter
    (alternatively set `DefaultIgnoreCondition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull` on the `JsonSerializerOptions` used by `EmitAsync` —
    prefer the property-level attribute to minimize blast radius).

    Test impact: 1 Skip'd test (`R2SseEventEmitterTests.EmitCapabilityChangeAsync_OmitsRetryAfterSecondsWhenNull` Fact) flips Skip -> Pass.
    Per NFR-04: commit message MUST cite "RB-T070-02" + resolution mode `repaired`.
  </prompt>

  <role>BFF production-fix engineer closing a LOW-severity real-bug ledger entry under repair-not-rewrite discipline.</role>

  <goal>
    `CapabilityChangePayload.RetryAfterSeconds` (~line 311) decorated with `[JsonIgnore(Condition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull)]`.
    The 1 Skip'd test passes when re-enabled. Ledger row RB-T070-02 → `repaired`. Existing tests (RetryAfterSeconds-present cases)
    continue to pass.
  </goal>

